Project minimum standards:
- Function or method names should be enough to describe the actions standing behind that function or method,
- More complicated code should be explained in comments, 
- Obey Service Locator pattern standards,
- Every Repository and View should be Unit tested, Logic and Controllers are optional,
- We commit code that is without build errors, and unit tests pass,
- Check in bugs using Issues GitHub option, bug description is mandatory, images are optional,
- Commits should be commented, comments must explain what work have been done, and what changes have been made,
- Do not commit anything directly into master branch, work on your local branch, to merge it to local do Pull Request,
- TO BE CONTINUED.
